io.jeo.ogr

Class OGR

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.jeo.data.FileDriver<T>
      • io.jeo.vector.FileVectorDriver<OGRWorkspace>
        • io.jeo.ogr.OGR
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Disposable, Driver<OGRWorkspace>, VectorDriver<OGRWorkspace>, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class OGR
extends FileVectorDriver<OGRWorkspace>
implements Disposable
    Driver for formats supported by the OGR/GDAL library.

    Usage: 

    
 Workspace ws = OGR.open('states.csv');

    Author:
    Justin Deoliveira, Boundless

      • close

        public void close()
        Description copied from interface: Disposable
        Disposes the object.

        Unlike Closeable.close() this method does not throw IOException and implementations must ensure no exceptions are thrown from this method.

        Application code must always be sure to call this method on any implementing class. Implementing classes should handle multiple calls to this method.

      • capabilities

        public Set<Driver.Capability> capabilities()
        Description copied from interface: Driver
        The driver capabilities that declare what operations the driver is capable of handling natively.

        For example, to check if a vector driver supports bounding box queries. 

           VectorDriver drv = ...;
   if (drv.capabilities().contains(VectorDriver.BOUND)) {
       // driver supports native bbox queries
   }

        Specified by:
        capabilities in interface Driver<OGRWorkspace>
